.TH "ata_sff_busy_sleep" 9 "ata_sff_busy_sleep" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ata_sff_busy_sleep \- sleep until BSY clears, or timeout
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ata_sff_busy_sleep
.BI "(struct ata_port *ap "  ","
.BI "unsigned long tmout_pat "  ","
.BI "unsigned long tmout "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ap" 12
port containing status register to be polled
.IP "tmout_pat" 12
impatience timeout in msecs
.IP "tmout" 12
overall timeout in msecs

Sleep until ATA Status register bit BSY clears,
or a timeout occurs.

LOCKING:
Kernel thread context (may sleep).
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno otherwise.
